The Agriculture Department recalled 14,000 jars of 4-ounce Vegetable, taking samples of Heinz products in response to a listeriosis outbreak.
Sara Lee Corp. also recalled hot dogs after a food poisoning outbreak.
No illnesses have been linked to the recalled products, but consumers are urged not to consume them.
The outbreak raises concerns about food safety procedures and the need for more testing.
The recall of contaminated meat highlights the importance of thorough cooking and proper food handling to prevent illness.
The investigation into the source of the outbreak continues, emphasizing the need for caution, especially for vulnerable populations.
